replies.bodyText:
Hmmm, how is that different from e.g. this line:
https://github.com/junit-pioneer/junit-pioneer/pull/318/files#diff-1d7cb2850ba029a8ff112abb5d62575aR30
Here and elsewhere one tab is used, whereas the above example uses two tabs. So:
assertThat(/* ... */).
		isNull();

// vs.

assertThat(/* ... */).
	isEqualTo(/* ... */);
